    IGameBoard
    public class GameBoardMem
extends AbsGameBoard
implements IGameBoard
    This class is used to contain our actual gameboard.
    Invariant:
    3 < NUM_WIN <= 100 AND NUM_WIN <= NUM_ROWS AND NUM_WIN <= NUM_COLUMNS AND 3 <= NUM_ROWS <= 100 AND 3 <= NUM_COLUMNS <= 100 AND [when accessing the board, BoardPositions be w/i bounds] -1 < BoardPosition.getRow() < NUM_ROWS AND -1 < BoardPosition.getColumn() < NUM_COLUMNS
    Correspondence:
    self = Map> AND number_of_rows = NUM_ROWS AND number_of_columns = NUM_COLUMNS AND number_of_wins = NUM_WIN

        public GameBoardMem​(int rows,
                    int columns,
                    int num_win)
        This constructor creates a new Gameboard represented by a Map with a key value pair. The key is the player's Character. The value is a List of BoardPositions.
        Pre:
        3 <= rows <= 100 AND 3 <= columns <= 100 AND 3 <= num_win <= 25 AND num_win <= columns AND num_win <= rows
        Post:
        board = new HashMap<>() AND NUM_ROWS = rows AND NUM_COLUMNS = columns AND NUM_WIN = num_win
        Parameters:
        rows - number of rows in the board
        columns - number of columns in the board
        num_win - how many tokens in a row to win the game
